You are conducting a sports event and you want to divide all the registered players equally into teams.
Given the total number of players and the number of players required per team, calculate:
The total number of teams that can be formed
The number of players who will be left out (not fitting into any team)
Input Format

The first line contains an integer totalPlayers
The second line contains an integer playersPerTeam
Constraints

1 <= totalPlayers <= 10^6
1 <= playersPerTeam <= totalPlayers
Output Format

Total teams formed: Players left out:

Sample Input 0

100  
11
Sample Output 0

Total teams formed: 9  
Players left out: 1
Sample Input 1

40  
5
Sample Output 1

Total teams formed: 8  
Players left out: 0

Code

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int totalplayers=sc.nextInt();
        int playerperteam=sc.nextInt();
        int team=totalplayers/playerperteam;
        int leftout=totalplayers%playerperteam;
        System.out.println("Total teams formed: " + team);
        System.out.println("Players left out: " + leftout);  
    }
}
